solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int findLUSlength(string a, string b) {
        if (a == b) return -1;
        return max(a.size(), b.size());
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(min(N,M))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The longest possible uncommon subsequence is the entire longer string itself, because if the strings differ, at least one of them is not a subsequence of the other. If the strings are identical, every subsequence is common, so return -1.

